# Frontend Rules

> Extends [root AGENTS.md](../AGENTS.md). Auto-loaded when editing `*.vue`, `composables/*.ts`, `stores/*.ts`.

## Always

- Use Highrise HL components (`HLButton`, `HLInput`, etc.) from `@platform-ui/highrise` — no raw HTML. [MUST]
- Use `v-model:value` (not `v-model`) for HL inputs; `v-model:show` (not `v-model:open`) for modals. [MUST]
- Wrap all user-facing strings in `$t()` or `t()` — no hardcoded English text in templates. [MUST]
- Use TanStack Query (`useQuery`, `useMutation`) for server state. [SHOULD]
- Use Pinia stores only for UI state that outlives a single component. [SHOULD]
- Use Highrise or CP design tokens (`--primary-*`, `--gray-*`, `--cp-*`, `--hr-*`) — no magic values. [SHOULD]
- Capture frontend errors with `@platform-ui/sentry` (`captureException`). [SHOULD]

## Never

- Never use `v-html` without `DOMPurify.sanitize()` — XSS risk. [MUST]
- Never use raw HTML elements where an HL component exists. [MUST]
- Never import from barrel files that cross layer boundaries. [SHOULD]
- Never store server-fetched data in Pinia — use TanStack Query. [SHOULD]

## Prefer

- Prefer `<HLButton variant="primary">` over custom button styling.
- Prefer composable functions in `composables/` for reusable reactive logic.
- Prefer `defineProps<{ ... }>()` with TypeScript generics over `defineProps([...])`.
- Prefer `useI18n()` inside `<script setup>` for programmatic translations.
- Prefer the matching framework overlay for frontend-specific rules (`vue`, `nuxt`).

## Verify

- Run `npm run type-check` before marking frontend work complete.
- Confirm no hardcoded English text exists in `<template>` blocks.
- Confirm all HL component imports resolve correctly.

